  "description": "Tyrannus kingbird by shape and yellow belly. Noticeably nothced dark gray tail with very slight light edges in perfect light but not light on outer webs of rectrices or on tail tips. Belly is quite yellow, not light yellow, from upper breast to undertail coverts. Back is light greenish in good light (see photos).\u00a0 Chin and throat are whitish. Forehead, head, and nape are light gray. Blackish bill is longish and stout.\u00a0\u00a0\n\n\r\nAlthough I did not hear the bird call, the recordings and spectrograms of its call on ebird (see and listen to Richard Bunn recording) eliminates all other kingbird species and eliminates hybrids with other flycatchers.",
